 of prayer, study and reflection is aptly mirrored in the architecture. Like the other Le Corbusier Guides published by Birkhäuser, this volume provides a wealth of plans, details, photographs and information on this building which today is also a conference centre.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aDominican monasterieszFrancezL'Arbresle. 4aArchitektur. 4aLe Corbusier. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Architecture, Design and Arts 2000 - 2014z9783110635690oZDB-23-GAA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLC Online Paketz9783035606034oZDB-23-LCO0 cprintz978376436298040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978303560314940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783035603149423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783035603149/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GAAc2000d2014  aZDB-23-LCO